INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (43401, 'The courage to admit when you''re wrong doesn''t show weakness. It shows your strength. Your integrity speaks volumes about you as a person.', 9412, 0), (43402, 'The problem is, we always want to pay the prices we can afford.', 5782, 0), (43403, 'The books you have read and the knowledge and inspiration you have gained can never be taken away from you.', 10395, 0), (43404, 'There is not a better time to start being the unique contribution that you are.', 5356, 0), (43405, 'Rather than risking feeling disappointed, they’re choosing to live disappointed.', 247, 0), (43406, 'The route to our highest hopes tends to run right through some dark, booby-trapped places. A girl needs a map and a light to steer her; she might need a flamethrower or a cannon as well. She might need a pirate lover.', 10396, 0), (43407, 'Just because someone tells you that you will never amount to anything doesn''t mean you have to prove them right. Prove them wrong by succeeding. There is no sweeter revenge than making someone eat their words. Even if they don''t admit they''re wrong about you, you will know.', 9412, 0), (43408, 'Solitary walks are great for getting new ideas. It''s like you''re in a video game and you pick up idea coins on the way.', 4583, 0), (43409, '..."la ficción es casi siempre copia de la realidad, o es exageración de la misma, o disimulo de lo que si ha ocurrido".', 10397, 0), (43410, 'The quest for enlightenment illustrates the paradox of desire—the fact that you must have desire to be motivated to transcend being ruled by desire.', 5746, 0), (43411, 'Birds Fly in the Sky, because they don''t know how to Cry! They know just one thing, to Sing!', 5635, 0), (43412, 'You can not live at all if you do not learn to adapt yourself to your life as it happens to be.', 141, 0), (43413, 'See it in yourself, and the world will follow suit. Believe in you.', 5766, 0), (43414, 'Face au questionnement sur l''existence de Dieu, se présentent trois types d''individus honnêtes, le croyant qui dit: «Je ne sais pas mais je crois que oui», l''athée qui dit: «Je ne sais pas mais je crois que non», l''indifférent qui dit : «Je ne sais pas et je m''en moque.»L''escroquerie commence chez celui qui clame: «Je sais !» Qu''il affirme : «Je sais que Dieu existe» ou «Je sais que Dieu n''existe pas», il outrepasse les pouvoirs de la raison, il vire à l''intégrisme ... En notre siècle où, comme jadis, on tue au nom de Dieu, il importe de ne pas amalgamer les croyants et les imposteurs : les amis de Dieu restent ceux qui le cherchent, pas ceux qui parlent à Sa place en prétendant L''avoir trouvé.', 6421, 0), (43415, 'Scent is such a powerful tool of attraction, that if a woman has this tool perfectly tuned, she needs no other. I will forgive her a large nose, a cleft lip, even crossed-eyes; and I’ll bathe in the jouissance of her intoxicating odour.', 587, 0), (43416, 'Everyone has their own purpose on this earth. It''s up to you to figure out what your purpose in life is. No one can make that decision for you.', 9412, 0), (43417, 'I once took a city with five men and a lame goat. If I can do that, you can convince the necromancers to pledge themselves to you. Do this or die.', 762, 0), (43418, 'I’d loved women who were old and who were young; those extra kilos and large rumps, and others so thin there was barely even skin to pinch, and every time I held them, I worried I would snap them in two. But for all of these: where they had merited my love was in their delicious smell. Scent is such a powerful tool of attraction, that if a woman has this tool perfectly tuned, she needs no other. I will forgive her a large nose, a cleft lip, even crossed-eyes; and I’ll bathe in the jouissance of her intoxicating odour.', 587, 0), (43419, 'The writings are built by imagination. Emotions fill the colours to them.', 5811, 0), (43420, 'A bad life doesn''t justify bad behavior. It''s time to stop playing the blame game and take responsibility for your own actions. You have control of your life from here.', 9412, 0), (43421, 'Never be defeated by roadblocks life throws in your way. Instead, conquer them. You are much stronger than you give yourself credit for.', 9412, 0), (43422, 'Cultivation of positive emotions, including self-love and self-respect, strengthens our inner resources and opens us to a broader range of thoughts and actions.', 124, 0), (43423, 'Your principles are your true north because they instruct how you will handle every situation, especially when there is no easy choice.', 10398, 0), (43424, 'An alternative — and better — definition of reality can be found by naming some of its components: air, sunlight, wind, water, the motion of waves, the patterns of clouds before a coming storm. These elements, unlike 20th-century office routines, have been here since before life appeared on this planet, and they will continue long after office routines are gone. They are understood by everyone, not just a small segment of a highly advanced society. When considered on purely logical grounds, they are more real than the extremely transitory lifestyles of the modern civilization the depressed ones want to return to.If this is so, then it follows that those who see sailing as an escape from reality have their understanding of sailing and reality backward. Sailing is not an escape, but a return to and a confrontation of a reality from which modern civilization is itself an escape. For centuries, man suffered from the reality of an Earth that was too dark or too hot or too cold for his comfort, and to escape this he invented complex systems of lighting, heating and air conditioning.Sailing rejects these and returns to the old realities of dark and heat and cold. Modern civilization has found radio, television, movies, nightclubs and a huge variety of mechanized entertainment to titillate our senses and help us escape from the apparent boredom of the Earth and the Sun, the wind and the stars. Sailing returns to these ancient realities.', 1742, 0), (43425, 'Big dreamers don''t always accomplish big things; however, big accomplishments always come from big dreams.', 10399, 0), (43426, 'There are times when the world is rearranging itself that the right person can change the world.', 3356, 0), (43427, 'Believe you can and you will be halfway there.', 3356, 0), (43428, 'Genuine awe connects us with the world in a new way.', 124, 0), (43429, 'What Is A Belief?', 10400, 0), (43430, 'True Happiness doesn''t come from Prosperity, Pleasure, and Power, but from PEACE.', 5635, 0), (43431, 'It doesn’t matter how physically fit or tough you are, if you fail to use natures computer between your ears.', 10401, 0), (43432, 'We all come into and go out of this world in the same way. The Destination is the same. The difference is the Journey. Some Enjoy it, some Don''t !', 5635, 0), (43433, 'Do What You Want; these are the 4 most frightening words brought to us by the Connection Revolution. If you want to sing, sing. If you want to lead, lead. If you want touch, connect, describe, disrupt, give, support, build, question—Do It. You will not be picked. But, if you want to pick yourself—go for it. The cost is that you own the results.', 2113, 0), (43434, 'It is so wrong to run away from your purpose – you may be running away with a solution that may solve the world’s problems or save mankind.', 10402, 0), (43435, 'Art invariably grows out of a period when, in general, the artist admires his own nation and wants to win its approval.', 97, 0), (43436, 'Someone who lives meaningfully for 30 years has lived a much longer Life than one who drifted through Life for 60 years.', 5635, 0), (43437, 'Real love allows for failure and suffering.', 124, 0), (43438, 'The starting place for radical re-imagining of love is mindfulness.', 124, 0), (43439, 'We all have the Wisdom to understand that sooner or later Life will end, but we don’t have the Willpower to Live be